description.value:
Large pedestalled goblet, wheelmade with clear ridges on interior and exterior. Direct rim, straight walls and body curving down to meet a hollow foot, which was added after production. Rim diameter 13.9cm. Made in a dark pink Aswan fabric, with numerous red, white and grey stone inclusions, as well as soft red fragments and a piece of shell.
Decorated with a red painted rim; below, a frieze demarcated by two black painted lines above and two black painted lines below filled in with red, surrounding a string of balls in a mix of red and black. Below is another frieze containing red and black garlands, finished with one black and two red painted lines below.

description.value: Fragment of a gold-glass bowl: fragment of a thin and shallow bowl.  Apparently made in an open or press-mould by assembling rods which were fused together. Rods in various shades of blue and white. One rod of transparent colourless glass has tiny groups of gold-leaf fragments, three in each group and made in the sandwich technique. Similar rods doubtless existed in the missing areas. Impressed into the inner surface of the bowl is a bull's eye with an outer band of aquamarine-blue, then a ring of dark blue and, at centre, an opaque white disc. This does not go through to the under-surface. Opaque white bands were also impressed. These do penetrate to the under-surface.

description.value: Dinos(?) fragment. Clay drab brownish grey, with cream slip on outside; paint dull brown, fired greyishin parts. Additions in purplish red and white. Lower part of body of a large open form (dinos?), thick walled bearing black -figure friezes on outside, interior painted. Main (upper) frieze; sphinx or griffin right (head missing), with edge of a second animal visible at left and blobs in field; red patches surrounded by double incisions on hind leg, red on alternate wing feathers and on neck. Below, paint band bearing red band flanked by narrow white bands, top edge of another frieze below. Inside decorated in 'Vroulian' manner, with three white lines and two red bands added across middle and edges of incised floral chains(?) visible above and below, picked out with added rows of white dots and red and white details.
